title: Bug 121170 - get column label from meta data object should return user recognizable strings
description: The application is not returning user recognizable strings when calling the 'get column label' function from the meta data object.
OB: Currently, the labels returned before extraction are null, while the ones after extraction are recognizable strings.
EB: The expected behavior is for the 'get column label' function to always return user recognizable strings, both before and after extraction.
SR:
Steps to reproduce: 
1. Access the meta data object in the application. 
2. Call the 'get column label' function. 
3. Observe the returned value to verify it is a recognizable string.
